//  Runtime Environment Settings and Definitions 
// ----------------------------------------------
//
// The following lines May need to be uncommented , depending on run mode (Calibre Interactive/Include/command line or other ).
//
// Input GDS/Cellname/System Definition .
//
//  LAYOUT PATH "CELLNAME.gds"
//  LAYOUT PRIMARY "CELLNAME"
//  18sl.header LAYOUT SYSTEM GDSII
//
//  Output Database/report 
//  DRC SUMMARY REPORT "CELLNAME.report" REPLACE HIER
//  DRC RESULTS DATABASE "CELLNAME.db" ASCII 
//
DRC MAXIMUM RESULTS ALL
DRC MAXIMUM VERTEX ALL
//
//  DRC CELL NAME YES CELL SPACE XFORM
//
virtual connect colon yes
DRC keep empty no
text depth primary
//
// Layout base layer = Nwell, Active, Poly, Nimp and Contact
LAYOUT BASE LAYER  WNi AAi GCi XNi XPi CSi
//
//
// The following statement May not work for some versions of calibre, so it is kept un-commented.
// Using this statement should prevent false flagging of offgrid violations by merging the
// data before checking offgrid.
//
//  Some cases can cause false errors due to layers from different input cells 
//  In such case please uncomment the below
//   LAYOUT MERGE ON INPUT YES
//
// These Flags May Generate False Flagging in the Report file ,and may be related to DRC run Environment.
// Please comment if needed.
//
flag skew yes
flag offgrid yes   
flag acute yes
